# CatScope (SBA 308A)

A single-page JavaScript web app that browses cat images using The Cat API.

## Features
- Fetches data from an external API using `fetch` + async/await
- Browse a paginated gallery of cats (GET)
- Filter by breed (GET)
- Save favorites (POST) and remove favorites (DELETE)
- Submit votes (POST)
- JavaScript organized into modules (`api.js`, `state.js`, `ui.js`, `main.js`)
- Basic event-loop safety: ignores stale API responses using a request id

## How to Run
1. Clone the repo
2. Open `index.html` with a local server (recommended):
   - VS Code: “Live Server”
   - Or: `python -m http.server` then open the provided localhost URL

